text.tspan: Antibiotic use in livestock vs. meat supply per capita, 2010
Antibiotic use in livestock, measured as the milligrams of total active ingredient used per kilogram of meat production
versus the average meat supply per capita, measured in kilograms per person per year.
Source: European Medicines Agency, European Surveillance of Veterinary Antimicrobial Consumption (2017) & Van Boeckel et al. (2015); UN
